        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-12-19T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-12-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="871" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d871">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/12–1948: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-12-19">December 19,
                            1948</date>.<lb/>[Received December 19—8:34 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>CAT plane took off approximately 4:40 p.m. this afternoon from Tientsin
                    Changkueichuang field under Communist small arms fire. Field now unsafe for
                    further flights. Only two CAT American employees able to board departing
                    plane.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
